cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and text analysis to predict academic performance from short texts on social media. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a likely category as the paper uses data from a popular social networking site, VK, to build the predictive model. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of continuous word representations to improve the generalizability and interpretability of the model. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper involves the retrieval and analysis of text data from social media to predict academic performance. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper involves building a predictive model using machine learning techniques.
